JWT security depends heavily on the secret key strength and algorithm configuration. Weak secrets are one of the most common JWT vulnerabilities, allowing attackers to crack the key offline and forge tokens.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```php
<?php
require_once 'vendor/autoload.php';

use Firebase\JWT\JWT;
use Firebase\JWT\Key;

class AuthController {
    // CRITICAL VULNERABILITY: Weak, hardcoded secret
    private $secret = 'secret123';

    public function generateToken($userId, $role) {
        $payload = [
            'user_id' => $userId,
            'role' => $role,
            'iat' => time(),
            // No expiration set - tokens valid forever
        ];

        // Using HS256 with weak secret
        return JWT::encode($payload, $this->secret, 'HS256');
    }

    public function verifyToken($token) {
        try {
            // Decodes without algorithm restriction
            $decoded = JWT::decode($token, new Key($this->secret, 'HS256'));
            return (array) $decoded;
        } catch (Exception $e) {
            // Leaks error details
            return ['error' => $e->getMessage()];
        }
    }

    public function login() {
        $username = $_POST['username'];
        $password = $_POST['password'];

        // Assume validation happens here...
        $user = $this->findUser($username, $password);

        if ($user) {
            $token = $this->generateToken($user['id'], $user['role']);
            echo json_encode(['token' => $token]);
        }
    }
}
```

**Attack Payload**:
```bash
# Step 1: Capture a valid JWT from network traffic
token="eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VyX2lkIjoxMjMsInJvbGUiOiJ1c2VyIiwiaWF0IjoxNjk0MDAwMDAwfQ.signature"

# Step 2: Crack the weak secret using hashcat
hashcat -a 0 -m 16500 $token wordlist.txt
# Result: secret123 (cracked in seconds)

# Step 3: Forge admin token with cracked secret
php -r '
use Firebase\JWT\JWT;
$payload = ["user_id" => 1, "role" => "admin", "iat" => time()];
echo JWT::encode($payload, "secret123", "HS256");
'
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Weak secret `secret123` can be cracked in seconds using dictionary attacks
- Hardcoded secrets end up in version control and are easily discovered
- No token expiration means stolen tokens work indefinitely
- Error messages leak JWT library information to attackers
- No audience/issuer validation allows token reuse across applications

**SECURE VERSION**:

```php
<?php
require_once 'vendor/autoload.php';

use Firebase\JWT\JWT;
use Firebase\JWT\Key;

class SecureAuthController {
    private string $secret;
    private string $issuer;
    private string $audience;
    private int $tokenExpiry = 3600; // 1 hour
    private int $refreshExpiry = 604800; // 7 days

    public function __construct() {
        // Load secret from environment - must be 256+ bits (32+ chars)
        $this->secret = getenv('JWT_SECRET');
        if (strlen($this->secret) < 32) {
            throw new RuntimeException('JWT secret must be at least 256 bits');
        }
        $this->issuer = getenv('JWT_ISSUER') ?: 'https://api.example.com';
        $this->audience = getenv('JWT_AUDIENCE') ?: 'https://app.example.com';
    }

    public function generateToken(int $userId, string $role): array {
        $issuedAt = time();
        $tokenId = bin2hex(random_bytes(16)); // Unique token ID

        $accessPayload = [
            'iss' => $this->issuer,
            'aud' => $this->audience,
            'iat' => $issuedAt,
            'nbf' => $issuedAt,
            'exp' => $issuedAt + $this->tokenExpiry,
            'jti' => $tokenId,
            'sub' => (string) $userId,
            'role' => $role,
            'type' => 'access'
        ];

        $refreshPayload = [
            'iss' => $this->issuer,
            'aud' => $this->audience,
            'iat' => $issuedAt,
            'exp' => $issuedAt + $this->refreshExpiry,
            'jti' => bin2hex(random_bytes(16)),
            'sub' => (string) $userId,
            'type' => 'refresh'
        ];

        return [
            'access_token' => JWT::encode($accessPayload, $this->secret, 'HS256'),
            'refresh_token' => JWT::encode($refreshPayload, $this->secret, 'HS256'),
            'expires_in' => $this->tokenExpiry,
            'token_type' => 'Bearer'
        ];
    }

    public function verifyToken(string $token, string $expectedType = 'access'): ?array {
        try {
            $decoded = JWT::decode(
                $token, 
                new Key($this->secret, 'HS256')
            );

            $claims = (array) $decoded;

            // Validate issuer and audience
            if ($claims['iss'] !== $this->issuer) {
                error_log('JWT issuer mismatch: ' . $claims['iss']);
                return null;
            }

            if ($claims['aud'] !== $this->audience) {
                error_log('JWT audience mismatch: ' . $claims['aud']);
                return null;
            }

            // Validate token type
            if ($claims['type'] !== $expectedType) {
                error_log('JWT type mismatch: expected ' . $expectedType);
                return null;
            }

            return $claims;

        } catch (Exception $e) {
            // Log internally, don't expose to user
            error_log('JWT verification failed: ' . $e->getMessage());
            return null;
        }
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Strong secret from environment**: 256+ bit secret loaded from env vars, never hardcoded
- **Short-lived tokens**: Access tokens expire in 1 hour, limiting exposure window
- **Issuer/audience validation**: Prevents token reuse across different applications
- **Token type claims**: Separates access and refresh tokens to prevent misuse
- **Unique token IDs (jti)**: Enables token revocation and replay detection
- **Generic error responses**: Internal logging without exposing details to attackers

Production JWT systems need token revocation, secret rotation, and comprehensive security monitoring. Here's a complete implementation with Redis-based blocklist and key rotation support.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```php
<?php
require_once 'vendor/autoload.php';

use Firebase\JWT\JWT;
use Firebase\JWT\Key;
use Predis\Client as RedisClient;
use Monolog\Logger;
use Monolog\Handler\StreamHandler;

class ProductionJWTService {
    private RedisClient $redis;
    private Logger $logger;
    private array $secrets; // Multiple secrets for rotation
    private string $currentKeyId;
    private string $issuer;
    private string $audience;

    private const ACCESS_TOKEN_TTL = 900; // 15 minutes
    private const REFRESH_TOKEN_TTL = 604800; // 7 days
    private const BLOCKLIST_PREFIX = 'jwt:blocked:';
    private const MIN_SECRET_LENGTH = 64; // 512 bits

    public function __construct() {
        $this->initializeLogger();
        $this->initializeRedis();
        $this->loadSecrets();

        $this->issuer = getenv('JWT_ISSUER');
        $this->audience = getenv('JWT_AUDIENCE');

        if (!$this->issuer || !$this->audience) {
            throw new RuntimeException('JWT_ISSUER and JWT_AUDIENCE must be configured');
        }
    }

    private function initializeLogger(): void {
        $this->logger = new Logger('jwt_service');
        $this->logger->pushHandler(
            new StreamHandler('/var/log/app/jwt.log', Logger::INFO)
        );
    }

    private function initializeRedis(): void {
        $this->redis = new RedisClient([
            'scheme' => 'tcp',
            'host' => getenv('REDIS_HOST') ?: 'localhost',
            'port' => getenv('REDIS_PORT') ?: 6379,
            'password' => getenv('REDIS_PASSWORD'),
            'ssl' => ['verify_peer' => true] // TLS in production
        ]);
    }

    private function loadSecrets(): void {
        // Support multiple secrets for rotation
        // Format: JWT_SECRETS={"kid1":"secret1","kid2":"secret2"}
        $secretsJson = getenv('JWT_SECRETS');
        if (!$secretsJson) {
            throw new RuntimeException('JWT_SECRETS environment variable not set');
        }

        $this->secrets = json_decode($secretsJson, true);
        if (!$this->secrets || !is_array($this->secrets)) {
            throw new RuntimeException('Invalid JWT_SECRETS format');
        }

        // Validate all secrets meet minimum length
        foreach ($this->secrets as $kid => $secret) {
            if (strlen($secret) < self::MIN_SECRET_LENGTH) {
                throw new RuntimeException(
                    "Secret '$kid' is too short. Minimum " . self::MIN_SECRET_LENGTH . " characters required"
                );
            }
        }

        // Current key ID for signing new tokens
        $this->currentKeyId = getenv('JWT_CURRENT_KID');
        if (!isset($this->secrets[$this->currentKeyId])) {
            throw new RuntimeException('JWT_CURRENT_KID not found in JWT_SECRETS');
        }
    }

    public function generateTokenPair(int $userId, string $role, array $metadata = []): array {
        $issuedAt = time();
        $accessJti = $this->generateSecureTokenId();
        $refreshJti = $this->generateSecureTokenId();

        // Access token - short lived, contains permissions
        $accessPayload = [
            'iss' => $this->issuer,
            'aud' => $this->audience,
            'iat' => $issuedAt,
            'nbf' => $issuedAt,
            'exp' => $issuedAt + self::ACCESS_TOKEN_TTL,
            'jti' => $accessJti,
            'sub' => (string) $userId,
            'role' => $role,
            'type' => 'access',
            'kid' => $this->currentKeyId
        ];

        // Refresh token - longer lived, minimal claims
        $refreshPayload = [
            'iss' => $this->issuer,
            'aud' => $this->audience,
            'iat' => $issuedAt,
            'exp' => $issuedAt + self::REFRESH_TOKEN_TTL,
            'jti' => $refreshJti,
            'sub' => (string) $userId,
            'type' => 'refresh',
            'kid' => $this->currentKeyId,
            'access_jti' => $accessJti // Link to access token
        ];

        $accessToken = JWT::encode(
            $accessPayload, 
            $this->secrets[$this->currentKeyId], 
            'HS512', // Use HS512 for stronger security
            $this->currentKeyId
        );

        $refreshToken = JWT::encode(
            $refreshPayload, 
            $this->secrets[$this->currentKeyId], 
            'HS512',
            $this->currentKeyId
        );

        // Log token generation for audit
        $this->logger->info('Token pair generated', [
            'user_id' => $userId,
            'access_jti' => $accessJti,
            'refresh_jti' => $refreshJti,
            'ip' => $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'] ?? 'unknown',
            'user_agent' => $_SERVER['HTTP_USER_AGENT'] ?? 'unknown'
        ]);

        return [
            'access_token' => $accessToken,
            'refresh_token' => $refreshToken,
            'token_type' => 'Bearer',
            'expires_in' => self::ACCESS_TOKEN_TTL
        ];
    }

    public function verifyAccessToken(string $token): ?array {
        return $this->verifyToken($token, 'access');
    }

    public function verifyRefreshToken(string $token): ?array {
        return $this->verifyToken($token, 'refresh');
    }

    private function verifyToken(string $token, string $expectedType): ?array {
        try {
            // Extract header to get key ID
            $parts = explode('.', $token);
            if (count($parts) !== 3) {
                $this->logger->warning('Invalid token format');
                return null;
            }

            $header = json_decode(base64_decode($parts[0]), true);
            $kid = $header['kid'] ?? null;

            if (!$kid || !isset($this->secrets[$kid])) {
                $this->logger->warning('Unknown or missing key ID', ['kid' => $kid]);
                return null;
            }

            // Verify with the correct secret
            $decoded = JWT::decode(
                $token, 
                new Key($this->secrets[$kid], 'HS512')
            );

            $claims = (array) $decoded;

            // Validate standard claims
            if (!$this->validateClaims($claims, $expectedType)) {
                return null;
            }

            // Check if token is revoked
            if ($this->isTokenRevoked($claims['jti'])) {
                $this->logger->warning('Revoked token used', [
                    'jti' => $claims['jti'],
                    'sub' => $claims['sub']
                ]);
                return null;
            }

            return $claims;

        } catch (\Firebase\JWT\ExpiredException $e) {
            $this->logger->debug('Token expired');
            return null;
        } catch (\Firebase\JWT\SignatureInvalidException $e) {
            $this->logger->warning('Invalid token signature', [
                'ip' => $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'] ?? 'unknown'
            ]);
            return null;
        } catch (\Exception $e) {
            $this->logger->error('Token verification error', [
                'error' => $e->getMessage()
            ]);
            return null;
        }
    }

    private function validateClaims(array $claims, string $expectedType): bool {
        if ($claims['iss'] !== $this->issuer) {
            $this->logger->warning('Invalid issuer', ['iss' => $claims['iss']]);
            return false;
        }

        if ($claims['aud'] !== $this->audience) {
            $this->logger->warning('Invalid audience', ['aud' => $claims['aud']]);
            return false;
        }

        if ($claims['type'] !== $expectedType) {
            $this->logger->warning('Token type mismatch', [
                'expected' => $expectedType,
                'actual' => $claims['type']
            ]);
            return false;
        }

        return true;
    }

    public function revokeToken(string $jti, int $expiresAt): void {
        $ttl = max(0, $expiresAt - time());
        if ($ttl > 0) {
            $this->redis->setex(
                self::BLOCKLIST_PREFIX . $jti,
                $ttl,
                '1'
            );

            $this->logger->info('Token revoked', ['jti' => $jti]);
        }
    }

    public function revokeAllUserTokens(int $userId): void {
        // Store user invalidation timestamp
        $this->redis->set(
            'jwt:user_invalidated:' . $userId,
            time()
        );

        $this->logger->info('All tokens revoked for user', ['user_id' => $userId]);
    }

    private function isTokenRevoked(string $jti): bool {
        return (bool) $this->redis->exists(self::BLOCKLIST_PREFIX . $jti);
    }

    private function generateSecureTokenId(): string {
        return bin2hex(random_bytes(32)); // 256-bit random ID
    }

    public function refreshTokens(string $refreshToken): ?array {
        $claims = $this->verifyRefreshToken($refreshToken);
        if (!$claims) {
            return null;
        }

        // Revoke the old refresh token (one-time use)
        $this->revokeToken($claims['jti'], $claims['exp']);

        // Also revoke the linked access token
        if (isset($claims['access_jti'])) {
            $this->revokeToken($claims['access_jti'], time() + self::ACCESS_TOKEN_TTL);
        }

        // Get fresh user data (role might have changed)
        $userId = (int) $claims['sub'];
        $userData = $this->getUserData($userId);

        if (!$userData || !$userData['active']) {
            $this->logger->warning('Refresh attempted for inactive user', [
                'user_id' => $userId
            ]);
            return null;
        }

        // Issue new token pair
        return $this->generateTokenPair($userId, $userData['role']);
    }

    private function getUserData(int $userId): ?array {
        // Implementation to fetch user from database
        // Returns ['id' => int, 'role' => string, 'active' => bool]
        return null; // Placeholder
    }
}

